        <title>Games with a good &quot;CATS&quot; one-pager?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@OnlyAnAlligator]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/u/onlyanalligator">@OnlyAnAlligator</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>While I think it’s a bit of a mixed success in some areas, the playbook design of Fellowship does a lot to bake those questions into play, GM-side through the Overlord playbook of course, but also player-side through player agendas, which are largely there as a reminder of the story we want to tell.</p>
<p>PBTA, in general, tends to offer a CATS in its GM agendas, although some games, of course, make better use of them in that regard than others.</p>
<p>The setup of Microscope incorporates a lot of the question of a CATS discussion in the opening setup; the palette, the bookends, and the one-sentence pitch.</p>
          </blockquote>
